P( A \cup  B \,|\, C)
P(A | C) + P(B | C)
A
B
A\cap B=\varnothing
(A\cap C)\cap (B\cap C)=\varnothing
 \begin{align*} P(A\cup B\mid C)&=\frac{P((A\cup B)\cap C)}{P(C)}\\ &=\frac{P((A\cap C)\cup (B\cap C))}{P(C)}\\ &=\frac{P(A\cap C)+P(B\cap C)}{P(C)}\\ &=\frac{P(A\cap C)}{P(C)}+\frac{P(B\cap C)}{P(C)}\\ &=P(A\mid C)+P(B\mid C). \end{align*} 
